    • generateAccNum

      public static java.lang.String generateAccNum()
      Generates number of the user's account

      Generated acc number has next format: AABB CCCC DDDD EEEE FFFF FFFF FFFF (no whitespaces) Where: AA - country code "BY" BB - 2 control digits CCCC - first 4 digits of bank's SWIFT-code "UNBS" DDDD - balance account (FROM 3019 to 3199) "3014" FFFF FFFF FFFF - personal acc number

      Returns:
      String number of the generated account

    • generateCardNum

      public static java.lang.String generateCardNum​(java.lang.String accNumber, java.lang.String paymentSystem)
      Generates number of the user's card

      Generated card number has next format: KLLL LLMM MMMM MMNN (no whitespaces) Where: K - payment system international code LLL LL - first 5 digits of bank's BIN-code "46101" MM MMMM MM - last 8 digits of user's account number NN - 2 control digits of an account number

      Parameters:
      accNumber - is a generated 12-digit account number
      paymentSystem - is a card's payment system user was choose
      Returns:
      String generated card number
